l of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705201,"age":109,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord William Periam was born in 1440, in Broadclyst, Devon, England, his father, Sir John William Periam, was 27 and his mother, Margaret Hone, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Lady Mary Periam. He died about 1550, in Exeter, Devon, England, at the age of 111."},"et":{"1440–about 1550":"1440–umbes 1550","1440–1550":"1440–1550","1448–Female":"1448–Surnud","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1413–Male":"1413–Surnud","1416–Female":"1416–Surnud","1448":"1448","1468":"umbes 1470","1413":"1413","1455":"1455","1440":"1440","1550":"1550","1470":"1470","about 1550":"umbes 1550","1549":"1549","1416":"1416","Broadclyst, Devon, England":"Broadclyst, Devon, England","Exeter, Devon, England":"Exeter, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1440–about 1550":"1440–noin 1550","1440–1550":"1440–1550","1448–Female":"1448–Kuollut","1470–Male":"1470–Kuollut","1413–Male":"1413–Kuollut","1416–Female":"1416–Kuollut","1448":"1448","1468":"noin 1470","1413":"1413","1455":"1455","1440":"1440","1550":"1550","1470":"1470","about 1550":"noin 1550","1549":"1549","1416":"1416","Broadclyst, Devon, England":"Broadclyst, Devon, England","Exeter, Devon, England":"Exeter, Devon, England"},"fr":{"1440–abou